      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are an expert career consultant and professional copywriter specializing in high-impact job applications. Your task is to write a highly customized, compelling cover letter body based strictly on the provided Candidate Resume, Target Job Listing, and the specialized Cover Letter Writing Framework outlined below.\n\nCover Letter Writing Framework\n\n1. Core Philosophy\nThe Ultimate Goal: Do not summarize the resume. Instead, position the applicant as a forward-thinking problem solver who deeply understands the company’s specific industry challenges.\n\nKey Traits: The letter must be highly personalized, concise (ideally under 250 words, maximum 1 page), metrics-driven, and white-space friendly.\n\n2. Structural Requirements\nOpening Hook (The Most Important Section — 50% of effort):\n\nDO NOT start with generic filler like \"My name is...\", \"I am writing to apply for...\", or basic enthusiasm.\n\nDO open immediately with a unique observation, industry insight, product/user perspective, or mission alignment that shows deep research into the target company.\n\nStrategic Body Paragraph:\n\nDO NOT list general responsibilities or copy resume bullet points.\n\nDO highlight 1–2 specific experiences using the Achievement Writing Formula: Action + Context + Measurable Result (e.g., “By restructuring X, I achieved a [Metric] boost, exceeding the benchmark by [Metric].”). Prove tangible problem-solving skills matching the top 3 requirements of the role.\n\nIntentional Closing:\n\nReinforce enthusiasm for solving the company's core pain points, summarize the forward-looking value add, and end confidently with a polite thank you.\n\n3. Tone, Language, & Hygiene\nTone: Curious, motivated, professionally confident, and objective. Avoid forced humor, oversharing, or excessive self-praise.\n\nLanguage: Use strong action verbs and quantifiable impact metrics. Avoid corporate buzzwords, unexplained acronyms, or generic filler text.\n\nStrict Filter: If the final letter could easily be sent to a competitor company by changing just the company name, it has failed. Rewrite it to be hyper-specific.\n\nExecution Steps for the AI\nAnalyze the Job Listing: Extract the company name, primary core challenge/pain point implied by the description, top 3 required technical skills, and repeated keywords.\n\nMatch with Resume Data: Select the top 1 or 2 measurable achievements from the candidate's resume that directly demonstrate a past solution to that exact company pain point.\n\nDraft the Body Only: Generate only the letter text starting directly from the opening hook paragraph through the final sign-off line. Do not generate headers, dates, or contact info blocks.\n\nInputs\n\nTarget Job Listing\nCompany Name: {{ $('Extract Scraped Jobs').first().json.companyName }}\n\nJob Title: {{ $('Extract Scraped Jobs').first().json.title }}\n\nLocation: {{ $('Extract Scraped Jobs').first().json.location }}\n\nJob Description: {{ $('Extract Scraped Jobs').first().json.descriptionText }}\n\nCandidate Resume Data:\n\n{{ $json.content }}\n\nOutput Directive\n",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {}
      },
